Table

What it is for

traffic.business_intake_leads

Temporary queue for businesses you manually add from the dashboard before/while importing them into Traze.

traffic.providers

The real public business/profile record Traze should display. This is the main table.

traffic.provider_services

Connects a provider to one or more services, with optional prices. Example: Casa de Cambio → Money Exchange.

traffic.services

Master list of searchable services. Example: Barber, Locksmith, Restaurant, Money Exchange.

traffic.specialties

More specific service variations. Example: service = locksmith, specialty = car lockout.

traffic.cities

Supported cities Traze knows as structured locations.

traffic.neighborhoods

Smaller areas inside a city. Optional, useful later for SEO/local discovery.

traffic.provider_stats_current

Current ranking/trust numbers for a provider: reviews, rating, rank score, response time, etc.

traffic.price_aggregates

Market price ranges by city/service. Example: barber in Laredo P25/P50/P75 prices.

traffic.business_claim_requests

When a business owner clicks “Claim Profile,” this stores the claim request and verification status.

traffic.page_candidates

SEO page inventory. Tracks which pages should exist: city pages, service pages, provider pages, etc.

traffic.page_internal_links

Internal SEO linking map between pages. Example: /us/laredo/barber links to related providers.

traffic.seo_rules

Config/rules for titles, meta descriptions, indexing rules, page templates.

traffic.sitemap_chunks

Tracks generated sitemap files/chunks for Google indexing.